JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg police are investigating the deadly stabbing of a teenager on Saturday night. It's believed the 16-year-old was killed during an incident outside a nightclub on Wessel Road in Rivonia. ER24 spokesperson Ross Campbell said the teen was declared dead on the scene. “ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at 10:45pm along with another private medical service to find the teenager lying in the street with a fatal stab wound to the chest. Security and SAPS were on the scene for further investigations.” [RIVONIA] Teenager killed in stabbing incidenthttps://t.co/KgadctBxk4#realhelprealfast pic.twitter.com/ClFxpqRSna 